        <section data-uuid="1639ed65649d4de28f6f95d235fc587c">
            <p data-uuid="d08db7d90e0d45aaa3e019276968d306">The southern colonies’ cash crops required a great deal of difficult work to grow and harvest. This meant a large workforce was needed. By the 1700s enslaved Africans, rather than indentured servants, had become the main source of labor.</p>
        </section>
